Collective MySQL Document:
- Should have every MySQL Call the back-end could need.

Login:
SELECT PasswordHash FROM Accounts WHERE Username = "INSERT USER FROM SEAN HERE" OR EMAIL = "INSERT EMAIL HERE";

Registration
INSERT INTO Accounts (FirstName, LastName, Username, Email, Address, City, Country, ZipCode, PasswordHash) VALUES ( INSET FROM SEAN HERE );

Setting Profile:
SELECT AccountID FROM Accounts WHERE Username = '$username';
INSERT INTO Profiles(AccountID, FavoriteGenres, FavoriteDirector, Biography, FavoriteActor, FavoriteMovie) VALUES ('$AccountId', '$FavoriteGenres', '$FavoriteDirector', '$Biography', '$FavoriteActor', '$FavoriteMovie');

Calling Profiles:

SELECT Accounts.AccountID, Accounts.Username, Profiles.FavoriteGenres, Profiles.FavoriteDirector, Profiles.Biography, Profiles.RateScore, Profiles.FavoriteActor, Profiles.FavoriteMovie FROM Accounts RIGHT JOIN Profiles WHERE Accounts.AccountID = Profiles.AccountID;



